arm64: dts: rockchip: widen rk3528 soc ranges for PCIe

The 132 PCIe node puts config reg + IO/MEM windows in the 0xfc000000
region, but 6.18.34's soc ranges only maps 0xfe000000+0x2000000, so the
dwc driver fails to translate them ("Missing config reg space", ranges
resolve to 0xffffffff). Mainline widened soc ranges to 0xfc000000+0x44000000
when rk3528 PCIe landed; mirror that. Must come after 132.

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528.dtsi	2026-06-13 11:44:42.869070772 +0800
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528.dtsi	2026-06-13 11:44:42.871049208 +0800
@@ -278,7 +278,7 @@
 
 	soc {
 		compatible = "simple-bus";
-		ranges = <0x0 0xfe000000 0x0 0xfe000000 0x0 0x2000000>;
+		ranges = <0x0 0xfc000000 0x0 0xfc000000 0x0 0x44000000>;
 		#address-cells = <2>;
 		#size-cells = <2>;
 
